<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d62fn1">Sent by the United States Military
                                Attaché, London, via Army channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-21">January 21,
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Personal and Top Secret Number 891.</p>
                        <p>I suggest that the press should be entirely excluded from <gloss target="#t_ARGONAUT1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Argonaut</hi></gloss>, but that each of us
                            should be free to bring not more than three or four uniformed service
                            photographers to take “still” and cinematograph pictures to be released
                            when we think fit. Please let me know if you agree.</p>
                        <p>There will of course be the usual agreement communiqué, or
                            communiqués.</p>
                        <p>I am sending a similar telegram to U. J.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>